\sum_{k=1}^{2n-1}\sqrt{k(4n-k)}<\pi n^2
n
\displaystyle x \in \left[\frac{k-1}{2n},\frac{k}{2n}\right)
\displaystyle \sqrt{1-x^2} > \sqrt{1-(k/2n)^2}
k = 1
2n - 1
(*)
\begin{align} \sum_{k=1}^{2n-1}\sqrt{k(4n - k)} = & \sum_{k=1}^{2n-1}\sqrt{(2n)^2-(2n-k)^2} =\sum_{k=1}^{2n-1}\sqrt{(2n)^2-k^2}\\ = & 2n\sum_{k=1}^{2n-1}\sqrt{1-(k/2n)^2}\tag{*} \end{align}
\int_{\frac{k-1}{2n}}^{\frac{k}{2n}} \sqrt{1-x^2} dx > \frac{1}{2n}\sqrt{1-(k/2n)^2}
 \sum_{k=1}^{2n-1}\sqrt{k(4n - k)} < (2n)^2 \int_0^{1-\frac{1}{2n}}\sqrt{1-x^2}dx < (2n)^2 \int_0^1\sqrt{1-x^2}dx = \pi n^2 
